Law Offices of Howard G. Smith Announces Class Action Lawsuit Against JPMorgan Chase & Co.
Thursday, 17 May 2012 09:15pm EDT
Law Offices of Howard G. Smith announced that a class action lawsuit has been filed in the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York on behalf of all purchasers of the common stock of JPMorgan Chase & Co. between April 13, 2012, and May 11, 2012, inclusive (the Class Period). On May 10, 2012, the Company revealed that the Company had sustained a multibillion dollar trading loss as a result of a risky strategy to hedge the Company’s credit exposure. In response to this disclosure, the Company's stock price declined from $40.74 per share to a closing price of $36.96 per share on extremely heavy trading volume 
